# EXPECTED RESULTS

## Legacy STP

| Behavior          | Result             |
| ----------------- | ------------------ |
| Convergence       | Slow               |
| Packet Loss       | High               |
| Transition States | Listening/Learning |
| Recovery Time     | 30–50 sec          |

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## RSTP

| Behavior          | Result   |
| ----------------- | -------- |
| Convergence       | Fast     |
| Packet Loss       | Minimal  |
| Transition States | Rapid    |
| Recovery Time     | ~1–5 sec |

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# WHAT YOU LEARNED

* Difference between 802.1D and RSTP
* Why legacy STP converges slowly
* RSTP rapid synchronization behavior
* Impact of convergence on real traffic
* Importance of fast failover in enterprise networks

